projectInfo.name: Missing Maps: buildings and residential areas in Niger State, Nigeria (project 15)
projectInfo.shortDescription: MSF teams working in Niger state, northern Nigeria, respond to a variety of different health needs. These include emergency response to disease outbreaks across the area. Accurate maps of the area will assist emergency teams with epidemiological analysis, disease surveillance and logistical planning.
projectInfo.description:
MSF teams working in Niger state, northern Nigeria, respond to a variety of different health needs. These include emergency response to disease outbreaks across the area. Accurate maps of the area will assist emergency teams with epidemiological analysis, disease surveillance and logistical planning.

The Missing Maps project aims to map the most vulnerable places in the world (affected by humanitarian crises: disease epidemics, conflict, natural disasters, poverty, environmental crises). Building on HOT's disaster preparedness projects, the Missing Maps tasks facilitate pre-emptive mapping of priority countries to better facilitate disaster response, medical activities and resource allocation when crises occur.

This task was generated through [Mapswipe](http://mapswipe.org/). All satellite imagery has been reviewed for containing buildings.
projectInfo.instructions:
Check this [guide](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1N_3G3EwYQjtJ_5c9FrbPMY7W7QjlLqGeZvDID8tH4Kw/edit?usp=sharing) to learn more of the work of MSF in the area and for some tips and tricks to help you in your mapping. Take also a look at this [Niger State pinterest board](https://www.pinterest.co.uk/TheMissingMaps/niger-state-nigeria/) to get to know Niger state a bit better and see what you will be mapping in this task! 


Imagery
========================
Please use the **Maxar Premium Imagery**. 

Buildings
=========================
Buildings are generally squared and round huts with straw or tin roofs. Please **map all** of them.  


**For rectangular buildings:** 
* In iD: draw an area and label it as “Building”, then correct for right angles with the “Q” key
* In JOSM: draw an area and use the tag “building=yes”; then correct for right angles using the “Q” key - OR use the building plugin

**For circular buildings:** 
* In iD: draw an triangular area over the building and use the tag "Building", then correct to make the shape circular with the "O" key
* In JOSM: draw a line on the diameter of the building and use the tag “building=yes”; then hit "Shift+O" to make the shape circular - OR use the building plugin

Please use also this [tracing guide](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1N_3G3EwYQjtJ_5c9FrbPMY7W7QjlLqGeZvDID8tH4Kw/edit#slide=id.g2b4a976497_0_15) to help you map buildings.



Settlements
=========================
Please **outline settlements with more than four buildings** as residential area. 

* In iD: draw an area and mark as *Landuse Features=Residential Areas*
* In JOSM: draw and area and mark as *landuse=residential*

Try to trace around all of the compounds, not just the buildings; the compounds often extend well past the inner circle of houses but are definitely part of the village. Usually the compounds have a fence around them.

If a residential area shape already exists, but does not encompass all the buildings in the village or town, please adjust the boundary accordingly.

Please use also this [tracing guide](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1N_3G3EwYQjtJ_5c9FrbPMY7W7QjlLqGeZvDID8tH4Kw/edit#slide=id.p6) to help you map settlements.

Roads and other features
========================
Your are **not requested** to map anything other than buildings and settlements in this project, however if you choose to, please check the [Highway Africa Tag page](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Highway_Tag_Africa) for advice on tagging roads and see [the OSM map features page](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Map_Features) for more information on general OSM tagging.

--------
**Note**: There are rare cases of settlements and buildings outside the task boxes, please map them too.

--------
